The bug in the code is that in the base case it's checking if array length is 0 which is incorrect. It should check whether length is less than or equal to 1 because when we have one element in the list, it is already sorted. 

Another issue is with extending the result array with the remaining elements from either left or right arrays. `result.extend(left[i:] or right[j:])` will only extend with one of them, not both. So, we should extend with remaining elements separately.

